#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:6
msgid ""
"Constraints are a way to control an object's properties (e.g. its location, "
"rotation, scale), using either plain static values (like the :doc:`\"limit\" ones </"
"rigging/constraints/transform/limit_location>`), or another object, called \"target"
"\" (like e.g. the :doc:`\"copy\" ones </rigging/constraints/transform/"
"copy_location>`)."
msgstr ""
"约束是一种使用静态数值 (如 :doc:`\"限制类\" 约束 </rigging/constraints/transform/"
"limit_location>`), 或者称作\"目标\"的其他对象(如 :doc:`\"复制类\" 约束 </rigging/"
"constraints/transform/copy_location>`)，控制对象属性(例如其位置、旋转、缩放)的方法。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:12
msgid ""
"Even though constraints are useful in static projects, their main usage is "
"obviously in animation."
msgstr "即使在静态项目中，约束都是非常有用的，其主要用途显然是动画。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:15
msgid ""
"You can control an object's animation through the targets used by its constraints "
"(this is a form of indirect animation). Indeed, these targets can then control the "
"constraint's owner's properties, and hence, animating the targets will indirectly "
"animate the owner."
msgstr ""
"可以通过其约束所使用的目标来控制物体的动画（这是间接动画的一种形式）。事实上，这些目"
"标可以控制约束的所有者的属性，因此，动画目标将间接驱动其所有者。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:19
msgid ""
"You can animate constraints' settings. e.g. the *Influence* or when using an "
"armature's bone as target, animate where along this bone (between root and tip) "
"lays the real target point."
msgstr ""
"可以驱动约束的设置，如 *Influence影响* ，或者在使用骨架的骨骼作为目标时，驱动沿着该"
"骨骼(根部和尖端之间)分布的真正目标点。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:23
msgid ""
"They can make the eyes of a tennis player track a tennis ball bouncing across the "
"court, allow the wheels on a bus to all rotate together, help a dinosaur's legs "
"bend at the knee automatically, and make it easy for a hand to grip the hilt of a "
"sword and the sword to swing with the hand."
msgstr ""
"约束可以使一个网球运动员眼睛跟踪网球弹跳地穿过球场，可以让一辆巴士所有车轮一起旋转，"
"可以帮助一只恐龙的腿在膝盖处自动弯曲，或者轻松地让手握住剑柄并挥动剑。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:28
msgid ""
"Constraints, in Blender, work with :term:`Objects <Object>` and :term:`Bones "
"<Bone>`. Read about using constraints in rigging in the :doc:`Armature chapter </"
"rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/index>`."
msgstr ""
"在Blender里，约束作用于 :term:`对象 <Object>` 和 :term:`骨骼 <Bone>` 。在 :doc:`骨架"
"章节 </rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/index>` 阅读约束在绑定中的使用。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:34
msgid "Object Constraints."
msgstr "物体约束。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:38
msgid "Bone Constraints."
msgstr "骨骼约束。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:40
msgid "Constraints work in combination with each other to form a Constraint Stack."
msgstr "约束可以相互组合，形成一个约束堆栈。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:44
msgid "The Constraint Stack is evaluated from top to bottom."
msgstr "约束堆栈是从顶部到底部进行运算的。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:48
msgid "Tips"
msgstr "Tips 小贴士"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:50
msgid "Constraints are a fantastic way to add sophistication and complexity to a rig."
msgstr "约束是一种神奇的方式，能够给绑定增加成熟度和复杂性。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:52
msgid ""
"But be careful not to rush in too quickly, piling up constraint upon constraint "
"until you lose all sense of how they interact with each other."
msgstr "但不要急着这么做，在搞不清楚约束之间如何交流的时候，就不要再叠加约束了。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/introduction.rst:55
msgid ""
"Start simply. Get to know a single constraint inside and out. :doc:`/rigging/"
"constraints/transform/copy_location` is a good first constraint to explore it also "
"has an animation example. Take the time to understand every fundamental concept "
"behind it, and the other constraints will make far more sense."
msgstr ""
"先从简单的开始。从里到外了解一个单一约束。:doc:`/rigging/constraints/transform/"
"copy_location` 作为第一个探索的约束就不错，它还有一个动画示例。花时间去了解它背后的"
"每一个基本概念，对其他的约束将有更多的理解感觉。"
